==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jacal
<hw>Ja*cal"</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧*k⟦aum⟧l"; 239)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Amer. Sp., fr. Mex. <ets>xacalli</ets>.]</ety> <def>In Mexico and
the southwestern United States, a kind of plastered house or hut,
usually made by planting poles or timber in the ground, filling in
between them with screen work or wickerwork, and daubing one or both
sides with mud or adobe mortar; also, this method of
construction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jacamar</ent>⟦br⟧
